<http://dx.doi.org/10.11646/zootaxa.3797.1.11>
    bibo:endPage "129" ;
    bibo:issue "1" ;
    bibo:journal "Zootaxa" ;
    bibo:startPage "120" ;
    bibo:volume "3797" ;
    dc:creator "Schwarz, Christian J.; Helmkampf, Martin" ;
    dc:date "2014" ;
    dc:title "A remarkable new species of Mythomantis Giglio-Tos, 1916 from northern Borneo, with notes on the systematics of Deroplatyinae Westwood, 1889 (Mantodea: Mantidae)" ;
    fabio:hasPart <http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.227431>, <http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.227432>, <http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.227434>, <http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.227433> ;
    a fabio:JournalArticle .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.227431>
    dc:description "FIGURE 1 – 3. 1. Habitus of holotype, dorsal view (large scale units: 10 mm). 2. Head of holotype, anterior view (scale: 1 mm). 3. Left fore femur and tibia of holotype, posterior view (scale: 2 mm)." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/227431/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.227432>
    dc:description "FIGURE 4 – 7. 4. Pronota. (a) Holotype; (b) paratype from Sarawak; (c) paratype from Sabah (scale: 5 mm). 5. Apex of left hind femur of holotype (scale: 1 mm). 6. Abdomen apex of holotype. (a) Supra-anal plate with cerci, dorsal view (hairs omitted); (b) subgenital plate, ventral view (scale: 5 mm). 7. Male genitalia. (a) Genitalia of holotype, ventral view (scale: 1 mm); (b) detail of phalloid apophysis of holotype, dorsal view; (c) and (d) phalloid apophyses of two paratypes, dorsal and ventral view, respectively (scale: 0.1 mm)." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/227432/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.227434>
    dc:description "FIGURE 9. Known distribution of the genus Mythomantis (after De Haan 1842, Werner 1921, 1922, 1925, 1928, Roy 2004 and this study): circles = M. confusa; squares = M. serrata; triangles = M. gracilis. Question marks indicate ambiguous locations (see main text). Map by Thomas Lessman (www. WorldHistoryMaps. info), used with permission." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/227434/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.227433>
    dc:description "FIGURE 8. Ventral phallomere and phalloid apophysis of Pseudempusa pinnapavonis (scale: 0.1 mm)" ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/227433/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

